      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The compound MON-0585 is a nontoxic, biodegradable larvicide that is highly selective against mosquito larvae. Synthesize MON-0585 using either benzene or phenol as a source of the aromatic rings.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBb29WIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--7ea97c517fe93bcf812015a2b51cc55555b6abd8/OChem_16_EC_042.jpg\" alt=\"MON-0585 has a central carbon bonded to a benzene ring, two methyl groups, and a phenol group, in which the two carbons next to the O H are each bonded to a tertiaru butyl group.\">",
